and circumambulating the funeral pyre three times
worshipped the Fortunate Ones feet with their heads
After the Fortunate Ones feet had been worshipped by venerable Mahākassapa
and by fivehundred monks the funeral pyre caught fire by itself
Now while the Fortunate Ones body was burning
of the outer skin the inner skin the flesh the sinews the synovial fluid
neither charcoal was evident nor was ash of the body left over
Just as while ghee or oil is burning
there is no charcoal and no ash evident
so when the Fortunate Ones body was burning
of the outer skin the inner skin the flesh the sinews the synovial fluid
neither charcoal was evident nor was ash of the body left over
Only two of those fivehundred pairs of clothes were not consumed
that on the inside and that on the outside
When the Fortunate Ones body was burnt
a shower of water appeared in the sky and the Fortunate Ones funeral pyre was extinguished
Also after water rose from a well
Also the Mallas from Kusinārā extinguished the Fortunate Ones funeral pyre with all types of fragrant water
Then the Mallas of Kusinārā
 after making an enclosure of spears in the Council Hall
and surrounding the Fortunate Ones bodily relics with bows
honoured respected revered and worshipped it
with dance song music garlands and perfumes
Then the Fortunate One addressed venerable nanda saying
Come nanda let us approach Koṭigāma
Very well reverend Sir venerable nanda replied to the Fortunate One
Then the Fortunate One together with a great Community of monks arrived at Koṭigāma
There the Fortunate One lived near Koṭigāma
There the Fortunate One addressed the monks saying
Because of a lack of understanding and a lack of penetration monks of Four Noble Truths
both you and I have been wandering and running along in Sasāra for a long time
Because of a lack of understanding and a lack of penetration monks of the Noble Truth of Suffering
both you and I have been wandering and running along in Sasāra for a long time
Because of a lack of understanding and a lack of penetration monks of the Noble Truth of the Arising of Suffering
both you and I have been wandering and running along in Sasāra for a long time
Because of a lack of understanding and a lack of penetration monks of the Noble Truth of the Cessation of Suffering
both you and I have been wandering and running along in Sasāra for a long time
 Because of a lack of understanding and a lack of penetration monks
of the Noble Truth of the Practice going to the Cessation of Suffering
both you and I have been wandering and running along in Sasāra for a long time
But now the Noble Truth of Suffering has been understood and penetrated
the Noble Truth of the Arising of Suffering has been understood and penetrated
the Noble Truth of the Cessation of Suffering has been understood and penetrated
the Noble Truth of the Practice going to the Cessation of Suffering has been understood and penetrated
Craving for continued existence has been cut off what leads to rebirth has been exhausted there is no continuation in existence
The Fortunate One said this and after saying this the Happy One the Teacher said something more
Because of not seeing as it really is the Four Noble Truths
we have run along for a long time through various births
Now these have been seen what leads to rebirth is uprooted
the root of suffering has been cut off there is no continuation in existence
There also the Fortunate One while living in Koṭigāma
spoke frequently to the monks about the Teaching saying
Such is virtue such is concentration such is wisdom
when virtue is welldeveloped it yields great fruit and brings great advantages in regard to concentration
when concentration is welldeveloped it yields great fruit and brings great advantages in regard to wisdom
when wisdom is welldeveloped the mind is completely liberated from the pollutants
that is to say the pollutant of sensuality the pollutant of craving for continued existence the pollutant of ignorance
Then the Fortunate One having gone down from the road
approached the root of a certain tree
and after approaching he addressed venerable nanda saying
